benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC19, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful modifications with valid headers and bodies.
Empty Response: @TC03 covers removal of all custom fields (empty array).
Non-Existing Resource: @TC05 covers non-existent bundle handling.
Invalid Input: @TC04, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC12 cover malformed JSON, missing body, unsupported parameters, and injection attempts.
Authorization: @TC06, @TC10 cover missing or invalid authentication headers.
Edge Cases: @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover maximum limits, partial updates, and backward compatibility.
System Errors: @TC11, @TC20 cover service unavailability and inconsistent data responses.
Performance: @TC17, @TC18 cover normal and peak load scenarios.
Regression: @TC19, @TC24, @TC25 cover previous fixes and backward compatibility.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under rapid or concurrent requests beyond concurrency tests.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Concurrency Control: No explicit tests for race conditions or optimistic locking during updates.
Authorization: No tests for role-based access control or token expiration scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to ensure proper handling of large datasets.
Include tests for rate limiting and throttling to verify system stability under load.
Implement scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation.
Create concurrency tests to simulate race conditions during updates.
Add role-based authorization tests to verify access control beyond missing headers.
